cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.LG 

This paper describes the development and evaluation of a meal-assistance system using a mobile manipulator robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The system is designed to assist people with motor impairments in eating independently, which involves human-robot interaction and assistive technology, making it relevant to the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the system with users, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of social and information retrieval (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG).
